    "content": "nullManage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Manage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\n Salesforce Billing Patch Notes\n Salesforce Billing Installation\n Salesforce Billing Overview\n Preparing Your Salesforce Org for Billing\n Managing the Billing Order\n Usage Rating and Processing\n Invoice Generation\n Applying Taxes\n Payments and Credits\n Understanding the Revenue Recognition Process\n The Revenue Waterfall\n Revenue Distribution Methods\n Organizing Your Revenue Transactions in a Revenue Schedule\n Revenue Transaction Balance Calculations for Invoice Lines and Order...\n Order-Based Revenue Recognition Reporting\n When to Create Revenue Schedules from Order Products\n Guidelines for Setting Up Order Product-Based Revenue Recognition...\n Considerations for Order-Based Revenue Recognition Reporting\n Creating Revenue Schedules with the Revenue Recognition Service\n Invoice-Based Revenue Recognition Reporting\n Configure Revenue Schedules to Use VSOE\n Revenue Schedule Fields\n Create a Revenue Schedule Manually\n Overriding Revenue Schedule Dates\n Validating Revenue Recognition Treatments\n Revenue Recognition Policies\n Revenue Agreements\n Revenue Adjustments\n Closing and Reopening Finance Periods\n Reporting Essentials\n Finance Logging\n Salesforce Billing Tableau Dashboards\n Understand What Your Customers Have Bought by Using Customer Asset...\n Printable Tip Sheets & User Guides — For Salesforce Billing\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALESFORCE BILLING\nOrder-Based Revenue Recognition Reporting\n\nGenerating revenue from order products allows high visibility into a business’s future revenue streams. When you create revenue schedules based on order products, you can forecast your future deferred revenue liability for the life of the specific performance obligation. Businesses using revenue forecasts for decision-making will have an up-front view of revenue forecasts for one-time and recurring products.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: All Salesforce Billing Editions\nWhen to Create Revenue Schedules from Order Products\nWhen deciding whether to recognize revenue from order products, consider key business needs regarding how your company uses revenue information in Salesforce Billing. For example, it’s important to know whether you’ll use Salesforce Billing for revenue forecasting or as the system of record to meet revenue recognition guidelines.\nGuidelines for Setting Up Order Product-Based Revenue Recognition Rules\nWhen you’re setting up order product-based revenue recognition rules, review important guidelines.\nConsiderations for Order-Based Revenue Recognition Reporting\nWhen you’re setting up invoice-based revenue recognition reporting, review important consideration\nCreating Revenue Schedules with the Revenue Recognition Service\nDevelopers can call the Revenue Recognition Service API to run revenue recognition for any Salesforce object in response to triggers, process builders, and REST API calls. The service is useful for recognizing or forecasting revenue on objects other than invoices, credit notes, and debit notes. For example, you could forecast quote line revenue following quote line approval, or recognize revenue after a contract is signed and activated.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
